Even as the Russia-Ukraine conflict continued, U.S. military giants are profiting from a steady stream of orders as government military expense rises. On March 28, the White House submitted the federal government budget application for fiscal year 2023 to the Congress, including a record defense budget application of $813 billion. In this episode of BizBeat, CGTN's Zheng Junfeng argues that U.S. budget has been bringing disasters to the world.